The UTM Philosophy Academic Society is a group of students interested in philosophy. There are -roughly- 1,940 students either enrolled in Philosophy POSTs or in at least one half-credit Philosophy course on the Mississauga Campus. The Philosophy Academic Society was setup to facilitate a comfortable, encouraging, and most-importantly, an engaging and fun environment for all students enrolled within the Philosophy program. We aim to;
i) provide academic help to philosophy students;
ii) act as the middle-wo/man between the Philosophy Faculty and its students;
iii) organise events to bring the department and its students together, and
iv) end lists with even numbers. We ordinarily meet on a weekday after 5pm for free refreshments and events such as guest speakers, movie nights, etc. We wish to acknowledge this land on which the University of Toronto operates. For thousands of years it has been the traditional land of the Huron-Wendat, the Seneca, and the Mississaugas of the Credit. Today, this meeting place is still the home to many Indigenous people from across Turtle Island and we are grateful to have the opportunity to work on this land. Read about U of T’s Statement of Land Acknowledgement. University of Toronto - Since 1827
